## Purpose
Create a systematic capture of Go library behaviors that serves as the "ground truth" for our Rust conformance tests. This involves running Go code and capturing outputs that we can compare against.

## Background & Reasoning

To verify our Rust implementations match Go, we need:
1. Known inputs
2. Captured Go outputs for those inputs
3. Comparison infrastructure

This task creates the Go-side test programs that generate reference outputs.

## Technical Approach

