 {"id":"charmed_rust-5x5.4.1","title":"Lipgloss Color Rendering Conformance","description":"## Overview
Tests conformance of all color rendering - ANSI 16, 256-color palette, true color (RGB), and adaptive colors.

## Color Types

### 1. Basic ANSI Colors (16)
- Black, Red, Green, Yellow, Blue, Magenta, Cyan, White
- Bright variants: BrightBlack through BrightWhite
- Codes 30-37 (foreground), 40-47 (background)
- Bright: 90-97 (foreground), 100-107 (background)

### 2. 256-Color Palette
- Colors 0-15: ANSI colors
- Colors 16-231: 6x6x6 color cube
- Colors 232-255: Grayscale ramp
- Format: ESC[38;5;Nm (fg) or ESC[48;5;Nm (bg)

### 3. True Color (RGB)
- Full 24-bit color support
- Format: ESC[38;2;R;G;Bm (fg) or ESC[48;2;R;G;Bm (bg)
- Range: 0-255 per channel

### 4. Adaptive Colors
- Changes based on terminal light/dark mode
- Light variant for dark backgrounds
- Dark variant for light backgrounds

## Test Matrix

| Color | FG Code | BG Code |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Red | 31 | 41 |
| Ansi256(100) | 38;5;100 | 48;5;100 |
| RGB(255,128,0) | 38;2;255;128;0 | 48;2;255;128;0 |

## Benchmark Suite
- bench_ansi_color_render - Render all 16 ANSI colors
- bench_256_color_render - Render all 256 colors
- bench_rgb_color_render - Render 1000 random RGB colors

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All ANSI color codes match Go exactly
- [ ] 256-color palette codes match exactly
